                <h1>How to Check Sapphire Authenticity: A Simple Guide</h1>
                <p>Sapphires are prized gemstones, but how do you ensure authenticity? Begin by checking color intensity and clarity. A genuine sapphire will exhibit deep, vivid hues, often with slight inclusions. Inspect the stone under UV light; genuine sapphires typically show a unique fluorescence. Consulting a gemologist is also recommended for peace of mind.</p>
